        <abstract> 
<p>Reports on the international support he has obtained for the zoological station [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7038</hi>]. Asks CD whether he will serve on a board of naturalists who would receive an annual report on the station.</p> 
            <p>Huxley is now convinced by AD’s views on homologies of the nervous system of arthropods, annelids, and vertebrates. Kovalevsky takes the same line but does not go far enough.</p>
        </abstract>
